<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>I’m very sensible, madam, of the hardship to my fair cousins, and could say much on the subject, but that I am cautious of appearing <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="forward and precipitate"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(鲁莽轻率)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But when the servants were withdrawn, he thought it time to have some conversation with his guest, and therefore started a subject in which he expected him to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="shine"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(表现突出)</code></b>, by observing that he seemed very fortunate in his patroness.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>You perhaps <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="allude to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(暗指/映射)</code></b> the entail of this estate.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Not that I mean to find fault with you, for such things I know are <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="all chance"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(全凭运气)</code></b> in this world.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>They chiefly <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="arise from"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(由……引起/产生)</code></b> what is passing at the time.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Has she been <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="presented"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(引见[给地位极高者]/受到觐见)</code></b>?</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I have more than once observed to Lady Catherine, that her charming daughter seemed born to be a duchess, and that <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the most elevated rank"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(最高贵的品阶)</code></b>, instead of <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="giving her consequence"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(提升她的显赫)</code></b>, would <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="be adorned by her"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(借重她为自己增光添彩)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Mr. Collins readily assented, and a book was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="produced"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(拿出/出示)</code></b>, but on beholding it, (for everything announced it to be from <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="a circulating library"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(流通图书馆)</code></b>,) he <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="started"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(惊跳)</code></b> back, and begging pardon, protested that he never read novels.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But here he was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="set right"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(矫正/纠正)</code></b> by Mrs. Bennet, who assured him with some asperity that they were very well able to keep a good cook, and that her daughters had nothing to do in the kitchen.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
